{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:53:50.720Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature selection"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "selecting the most relevant features from a dataset"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to use when building ML models by identifying important features that contribute to predictive power and removing irrelevant or redundant ones, thereby improving model accuracy and reducing overfitting."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \"While feature engineering creates new features, feature selection identifies the most important ones. It removes irrelevant or redundant features to improve efficiency and reduce model complexity.\""}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Feature Selection — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why feature selection matters"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduces overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwid